    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/org/computational-biofluid-lab",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed at Model Risk Level 5. Achieved levels meet or exceed required levels for every factor. Monte Carlo UQ (5000 samples) confirms NIH prediction intervals are bounded and all experimental measurements fall within 95% prediction intervals. Validation error metric E/U_val < 1.0 at all five operating points. Global sensitivity analysis demonstrates that uncertainty is dominated by the power-law exponent, which is bounded by calibration evidence. Software QA, code verification (MMS, observed order 1.97), and discretization error (GCI 2.8%) are all within required bounds. Independent reproduction and use-error controls are in place. The structured evidence base is complete and internally consistent; no credibility gaps remain. Decision: Accepted.",
